"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkinformationtoolbench=globalThis.webpackChunkinformationtoolbench||[]).push([[9206],{589(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"webapp-0.0.7","metadata":{"permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/webapp-0.0.7","source":"@site/changelog/webapp/2026-02-25-webapp-0.0.7/index.md","title":"0.0.7 (WebApp)","description":"We\'re excited to announce version 0.0.7 of the ITB WebApp (Information Technology Blueprint), bringing significant improvements to the user interface and data model capabilities. This release includes 10 new features and 1 important bug fix.","date":"2026-02-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"ITB APP","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/app","description":"All changes related to the ITB Application"},{"inline":false,"label":"UI","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/ui","description":"User interface changes"},{"inline":false,"label":"Model","permalink":"/docs/changelog-webapp/tags/model","description":"Data model changes"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"webapp-0.0.7","title":"0.0.7 (WebApp)","authors":[],"tags":["app","ui","model"]},"unlisted":false},"content":"We\'re excited to announce version 0.0.7 of the ITB WebApp (Information Technology Blueprint), bringing significant improvements to the user interface and data model capabilities. This release includes 10 new features and 1 important bug fix.\\n\\n> **Part of ITB 0.0.7 release** - See [master release](/changelog/itb-0.0.7) and [API Details](/changelog-api/api-0.0.7)\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \u2728 New Features\\n\\n### UI Enhancements\\n\\nThis release brings substantial improvements to the user experience with 8 new UI features:\\n\\n#### 1. Model Filter for Entity Type\\n\\nFilter viewpoint displays by entity type to reduce visual complexity. A new funnel button in the model canvas toolbar allows you to toggle visibility of entity types, helping you focus on what matters most.\\n\\n**Key Benefits:**\\n- Improved readability of complex models\\n- Focus on relevant entity types\\n- Quick toggle on/off for each type\\n\\n![Model Filter for Entity Type](./ui-001-new_model-filter-entity-type_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 3. Add Entity to Center of Canvas\\n\\nEntities are now added to the center of the visible canvas area rather than at a fixed position, providing a more intuitive editing experience.\\n\\n![Add Entity to Center of Canvas](./ui-003-new_add-entity-to-center-of-canvas_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 4. Entity Usage Indicator Across Viewpoints\\n\\nNew visual indicator shows where entities are used across different viewpoints, making it easier to understand entity relationships and dependencies throughout your model.\\n\\n![Entity Usage Indicator](./ui-004-new_usage-of-enitity-in-viewpoints-indicator_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 5. Edge Highlighting for Selected Entity\\n\\nWhen selecting an entity, all connected edges are now highlighted, making it easier to trace relationships and understand connections at a glance.\\n\\n![Edge Highlighting for Selected Entity](./ui-005-new_edge-highlighting-for-selected-entity_001.png)\\n![Edge Highlighting Example 2](./ui-005-new_edge-highlighting-for-selected-entity_002.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 6. Attribute Drawer with Pagination\\n\\nThe drawer concept has been extended to attributes, now accessible via **CTRL+4**. All drawers (viewpoints, entities, relations, and attributes) are now paginated, significantly improving performance in large models.\\n\\n**Available Shortcuts:**\\n- **CTRL+1** - Viewpoints\\n- **CTRL+2** - Entities\\n- **CTRL+3** - Relations\\n- **CTRL+4** - Attributes (New!)\\n\\n![Attribute Drawer](./ui-006-new_attribute-drawer_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 7. Save Canvas as Image\\n\\nExport your viewpoint canvas as a high-quality image for documentation, presentations, or sharing with stakeholders.\\n\\n![Save Canvas as Image](./ui-007-new_save-canvas-as-image_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 8. Auto Arrange Canvas\\n\\nAutomatically arrange entities in your viewpoint for optimal layout. A layout algorithm now helps organize complex models with minimal manual effort.\\n\\n![Auto Arrange Canvas](./ui-008-new_auto-arrange-canvas_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### 9. Resizable Left Sidebar\\n\\nThe left sidebar can now be resized to accommodate different screen sizes and user preferences, providing more flexibility in workspace organization.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Model Improvements\\n\\n#### 10. Mandatory Attribute Field\\n\\nAttributes can now be marked as mandatory using a new boolean field. This enhancement provides:\\n\\n- Clear documentation of required fields\\n- Better data quality and validation rules\\n- Support for generating database schemas with NOT NULL constraints\\n- Backward compatibility (defaults to `false`)\\n\\n**Display Features:**\\n- Visual indicator `*` (asterisk) in table columns to mark mandatory fields\\n- Compact icon-based display saves screen space compared to text labels\\n- Consistent indicator across main canvas, entity attributes table, and sidebar panels\\n\\n**Example:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\"id\\": \\"attr_123\\",\\n  \\"name\\": \\"customer_id\\",\\n  \\"type\\": \\"string\\",\\n  \\"mandatory\\": true,\\n  \\"description\\": \\"Unique customer identifier\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udc1e Bug Fixes\\n\\n### 2. Model Edge Routing on Collapse\\n\\nFixed an issue where edge routing was not properly updated when collapsing entity nodes in the canvas, ensuring proper visual representation of relationships.\\n\\n![Model Edge Routing on Collapse Fix](./ui-002-fix_model-edge-routing-on-collapse_001.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nVersion 0.0.7 represents a significant step forward in usability, performance, and data model capabilities. The UI improvements make working with large models more efficient, while the new mandatory field enhances data modeling best practices.\\n\\nThank you to all contributors and users who provided feedback!"}]}}')}}]);